                        SCHEMA SUMMARY
=============================================================================

Total Collections: 7
- users
- properties
- reservations
- payments
- reviews
- wishlists
- configs

Total Indexes: 16
- users: 0 (⚠️ email should be indexed)
- properties: 4 (owner, localisation.gouvernorat, localisation.delegation, prix)
- reservations: 3 (compound: property+dateDebut+dateFin, client, status)
- payments: 3 (reservation, client, status)
- reviews: 2 (reservation unique, property)
- wishlists: 1 (user unique)
- configs: 0 (⚠️ key should be indexed)

Relationships:
- One-to-Many: User → Properties, User → Reservations, Property → Reservations
- One-to-One: Reservation → Review (unique constraint)
- One-to-Many: Reservation → Payments
- Many-to-Many: User ↔ Properties (via Wishlist)

Missing Indexes (Recommendations):
1. users.email (unique, for login queries)
2. configs.key (for faster config lookups)
3. reviews.reviewer (for "my reviews" queries)
4. Compound index: (properties.owner, properties.isActive) for dashboard queries
5. Compound index: (reviews.property, reviews.rating) for rating aggregation

Data Integrity Issues:
1. No cascading deletes defined (orphaned records possible)
2. Wishlist can contain deleted/inactive properties
3. Reservations remain if property deleted
4. No foreign key validation in application layer
5. No audit trail for changes

